<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ANALYZE THIS, CHAN HO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ Paging Dr. Harding.... Paging Dr. Harding.
</P>
<P>
   It might be time to bring in Los Angeles Dodgers team
psychiatrist Herndon Harding to try to make sense out of what's
become of pitcher Chan Ho Park. No one else can.
</P>
<P>
   Park's fastball is in the mid 90s, his curve has plenty of bite
and yet his results are brutal. Even Park himself admits his 4-7
mark and gaudy 6.19 ERA are more a product of his mind than his
arm. Everyone else seems to agree.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's all mental,'' Dodgers manager Davey Johnson said. ``If
you think you can hit a guy, you hit a guy. If you think you can
get him out, you get him out.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson, one of the more cerebral managers, was asked if a
psychiatrist could help a player shake a funk.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe it. Absolutely,'' Johnson said. ``Whether it was
Frank Robinson talking to himself in the on-deck circle so he knew
what he was going to do before he got to the plate.... When you
picture what you're going to do, it's easier to do. You can talk to
yourself, just don't talk too loud.''
</P>
<P>
   Park was the Dodgers' No. 2 starter who would complement ace
Kevin Brown. But Park last won on May 26, and in his six starts
he's allowed 32 earned runs in 32 innings. Since being suspended in
early June, Park is 0-4 with a 10.71 ERA.
</P>
<P>
   The youthful Park (he's 26) has outside influences working
against him, which he hasn't handled well. He's the biggest sports
star in his native Korea, a pressure he realizes, and he's got a
contract to think about. Though he's eligible only for salary
arbitration after the season, he said he was affected by long-term
contract talks during the first month of the season. He's never
recovered.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's letting everything affect him,'' Johnson said. ``Part of
it's experience. You have to be able to put that shield over him.''
</P>
<P>
   What the Dodgers are hoping _ nearly on blind faith, the way
things have gone _ is that Park turns it around soon, as he did a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Park went 7-5 with a 4.76 ERA before the all-star break in 1998.
He was 8-4 with a 2.78 ERA after the break. In his career, Park is
17-12 with a 3.94 ERA before the break and 17-10 with a 3.31 ERA
afterward.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a concentration thing with him,'' pitching coach Claude
Osteen said after Park threw a bullpen session. ``He admits it.
Last year he thought negative things out on the mound and replaced
them with positives. He's not been able to do that this year.''
</P>
<P>
   Park is slated to start the series finale against the Colorado
Rockies on Thursday afternoon. Of course, this might not be the
best place for him to begin a turnaround. He's 1-1 with an 11.57
ERA at Coors Field.
</P>
<P>
   Watch your head: Now this is when you know things aren't going
well. Jason Repko, the Dodgers' top pick in last month's amateur
draft, missed the last week after suffering a mild concussion when
he was hit with a baseball _ thrown by one of his teammates.
</P>
<P>
   Repko, a shortstop playing with Great Falls (Mont.) in the
Pioneer League, was knocked out on a peculiar play. Center fielder
Shane Victorino fielded the ball and attempted to throw home, only
to hit Repko in the head.
</P>
<P>
   Repko, who's hitting .318, is expected to miss another few days.
</P>
<P>
   Balks, walks and chalk: Johnson said shortstop Mark
Grudzielanek, who went 1 for 2 in four innings in his third day of
rehabbing with Single-A San Bernardino, probably won't rejoin the
club until it returns home Friday for three games against
Seattle.... Reliever Antonio Osuna could begin a rehab with San
Bernardino as early as today.... Third baseman Adrian Beltre
returned to the lineup after missing two games with a strained left
groin.... Right fielder Raul Mondesi, who left Sunday's game with
tightness in his right leg, started against the Rockies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
