<P>
   INSURANCE-FRAUD (Nashville, Tenn.) _ Even in the early days of
what would become one of the largest insurance frauds in the
nation's history, a top Tennessee insurance examiner noticed that
Franklin American Corp. was reporting stratospheric profits on
garden-variety bonds. By Joseph Kahn.
</P>
<P>
   3M-OUTLOOK (St. Paul, Minn.) _ Here at the technology center of
Minnesota Mining and Manufacturing Corp., scientists are excited
about a new technology called microreplication, which they regard
as the road to product nirvana. But the mood is a bit more somber
across the street, where the corporate types cannot shake Wall
Street's perception of 3M as a boring, low-technology drone whose
glory days ended with Scotch tape. By Claudia H. Deutsch.
</P>
