<P>
   QWEST-FRONTIER (Undated) _ Over the weekend, while other
Americans grilled burgers, Joseph Nacchio and other Qwest
Communications executives gathered in Denver and New York to begin
preliminary merger discussions with executives from both Frontier,
the fifth-largest long-distance telephone company, and U S West,
the smallest of the regional Bells. By Laura M. Holson.
</P>
<P>
   FINGERHUT-INTERNET (Undated) _ When Wal-Mart Stores Inc.
announced late last month that it had hired Fingerhut Cos. to
process orders and handle distribution over the Internet, it sent a
delicious little jolt through the retail industry. By Leslie
Kaufman.
</P>
<P>
   CNET-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ CNET was one of the very first
companies to build a business on the World Wide Web, but it has
rarely benefited from the special dispensations that investors
accord most Internet companies. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   QUESTIONS-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ It's time again to ask 20
questions about advertising, marketing and the media. By Stuart
Elliott.
