r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-EYES-RUMORS-KAN &LR;      07-06 0646
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EYES-RUMORS-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LIPS ARE SEALED ABOUT `EYES WIDE SHUT' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ROBERT W. BUTLER  
 c. 1999 The Kansas City Star   ``Eyes Wide Shut,'' a movie
virtually nobody has seen, has tongues wagging and the Internet
humming with hearsay and speculation about what the film may show.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Its allegedly sexually explicit nature and the star power of
real-life married couple Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman have set the
rumor mills rumbling and led to widespread curiosity _ and, in some
cases, apprehension.
</P>
<P>
   Most film buffs view the release of any new movie from reclusive
director Stanley Kubrick as a major event. The man made only 13
films in his career (the last was ``Full Metal Jacket'' in 1987),
and most of those are considered classics.
</P>
<P>
   Add to this the fact that Kubrick died in March, just a week
after completing the editing of the movie, and ``Eyes Wide Shut''
becomes even more of a cinematic Holy Grail, the final testament of
a movie giant.
</P>
<P>
   ``This movie has a lot going for it coming out of the box,''
Nancy Kirkpatrick, senior vice president for publicity for Warner
Bros., said by telephone from Los Angeles. ``You've got Stanley
Kubrick, Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman. It's hard not to pay
attention.
</P>
<P>
   ``And then you add to that the fact that Cruise and Kidman are
naked.''
</P>
<P>
   Undoubtedly it's the sexthat keeps ``Eyes Wide Shut's'' hype
machine running on overtime.
</P>
<P>
   The first glimpse of Kubrick's footage came in March, when he
released to an exhibitors' convention a snippet of a nude Cruise
and Kidman in the early stages of making love. The images are
widely available on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've heard a couple of commentators mention that Kubrick never
made movies about sex,'' said KXTR radio personality Patrick Neas,
who describes himself as a major fan of the director's.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think almost all of his movies were about sex, only he took
a very dark view of it. Now for him to be looking back on the
subject as an older man and summing up his attitudes _ I think the
movie will probably be dark and nasty but very intriguing.''
</P>
<P>
   Others are less enthusiastic.
</P>
<P>
   Mary, a Johnson County restaurant employee who declined to be
identified by her last name, said she was concerned that the
combination of Cruise, Kidman and the R-rated movie's supposedly
lurid elements would be a magnet for impressionable young people.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've talked to teen-agers, and they're really eager to see
this movie,'' she said. ``I think a lot of people who normally
won't go see a movie with nudity or sex will come to see this one
just because Cruise and Kidman are so famous.''
</P>
<P>
   Then there's the rumor (the result of an early review of ``Eyes
Wide Shut'' written by a British friend of the Kubrick family) that
Cruise's character has a sexual relationship with a dead woman.
</P>
<P>
   ``Necrophilia?'' marveled a worried film booker for a local
theater chain. ``Maybe that flies on the West or East coasts, but
here in the Midwest? People aren't going to want to see that.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile hard facts about ``Eyes Wide Shut'' are hard to come
by. A television commercial being shown in 30- and 60-second
versions emphasizes suspense elements and is made up of seemingly
random images without dialogue.
</P>
<P>
   Screenings for theater owners originally planned for last
Thursday were called off; they were to be rescheduled this week.
Critics around the country won't see the film until just a couple
of days before its July 16 opening.
</P>
<P>
   And while Cruise's and Kidman's handsome features stare out at
us from the magazine racks (the stars are gracing the current
covers of Time, Vogue, US, Rolling Stone, Harper's Bazaar ... even
Good Housekeeping), the stories inside are uniformly devoid of
details about the movie's content.
</P>
<P>
   So it seems that the less we know about ``Eyes Wide Shut,'' the
noisier the buzz.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
