   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KNAPP-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ For women sportswriters, the ones
who know the rules of their business, the big story out of
Wimbledon last week was a disaster. Basketball star Julius Erving
confirmed that he had engaged in an extramarital affair with
Samantha Stevenson, a sportswriter who had covered his team, and
that their liaison had produced a child, rising tennis star
Alexandra Stevenson. By GWEN KNAPP.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-GOLF-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ Northern California's own Juli
Inkster has insisted on sharing the spotlight on her great year in
golf with husband Brian and daughters Hayley and Cori, partly
because she credits them for her resurgence at age 39. By SUSAN
FORNOFF.
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ For dogs, San Francisco is
paradise compared to any other city in America. And measured
against any other region anywhere, Northern California is just
about doggy heaven. By TOM STIENSTRA.
</P>
