   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ Where I was brought up there were
three things you didn't talk about: sex, money and patriotism. In
New England, these are powerfully private matters. In my family, at
least, flag wavers are as distrusted as those who flaunt their
wealth or sexual conquests. Where I live now there is only one
thing you don't talk about: patriotism. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   SALTER-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ As far as you can see down the
line of Republican candidates for president, you find no one
willing to trust women with their own reproductive systems. Every
person who has even an outside chance at the GOP nomination _ and
thus a shot at the White House _ is anti-choice. By STEPHANIE
SALTER.
