<HEADLINE>
`AFFLICTION' COMPELLING; `HILARY AND JACKIE' GRIPPING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Affliction'' _ Paul Schrader's stirring
adaptation of Russell Banks's searing novel about fathers and sons
was one of last year's most compelling films, as bleak as the New
Hampshire landscape it portrays. Nick Nolte, James Coburn, and the
overlooked, but not overshadowed, Sissy Spacek and Willem Dafoe
give great performances. See the movie, read the novel.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hilary and Jackie'' _ This tale of talent and madness, and two
sisters tragically linked, is grippingly told. Emily Watson, who
was superb in ``Breaking the Waves,'' is just as convincing in this
one, as cellist Jacqueline Du Pre.
</P>
<P>
   ``Desert Winds'' _ For those who appreciate art films, this
little number is worth renting. Michael Nickles's 1995 film is
being released on video, no doubt, because of the presence of
Hollywood's latest femme, Heather Graham. Although she gives a
terrific performance, she's not the only reason to watch this truly
independent film. Nickles, who also stars, brings an able eye with
both his camerawork and casting. Look for Adam Ant and B-movie
bombshell Monique Parent.
</P>
<P>
   ``The King and I'' (cartoon): This animated adaptation of the
live-action film that starred Yul Brynner and Deborah Kerr is
inadequate. The drawings are thin and flimsy, and the characters
are as flat as the artists who drew them. Even the songs seem trite
and silly.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING VHS ATTRACTIONS: July 13: ``A Civil Action,'' ``Central
Station,'' ``The Vicar of Dibley,'' ``Waco: The Rules of
Engagement.'' July 20: ``8MM,'' ``The General,'' ``Down in the
Delta,'' ``Virus,'' ``Mercenary 2,'' ``Double Platinum,''
``Resurrection Man.'' July 27: ``Baby Geniuses,'' ``October Sky,''
``Naked City.'' Aug. 3: ``A Midsummer Night's Dream,'' ``Tango,''
``Cruel Intentions,'' ``Message in a Bottle,'' ``Runnin' Wild: The
Films of Clara Bow.'' Aug. 10: ``Shakespeare in Love,'' ``True
Crime,'' ``The Mod Squad,'' ``Lock, Stock and Two Smoking
Barrels,'' ``The Deep End of the Ocean,'' ``Celebrity.'' Aug. 17:
``Analyze This,'' ``200 Cigarettes.'' Aug. 31: ``Cleopatra.'' Sept.
14: ``The Prince of Egypt,'' ``God Said Ha!,'' ``Children of
Heaven.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS ON DVD: July 6: ``Aria,'' ``Brute Force,''
``Wing Commander.'' July 13: ``A Civil Action,'' ``Dangerous
Minds,'' ``Immortals,'' ``Linnea in Monet's Garden,'' ``Little
Voice,'' ``She's All That,'' ``Spy Hard,'' ``Your Friends and
Neighbors.'' July 20-30: ``8mm,'' ``Always,'' ``Baby Geniuses,''
``Blast From the Past,'' ``Cool Runnings,'' ``Down in the Delta,''
``Dream Lover,'' ``The General,'' ``I Love Trouble,'' ``Little
Buddha,'' ``Mallrats,'' ``Mr. Holland's Opus,'' ``October Sky,''
``Pallbearer,'' ``Payback,'' ``Restoration,'' ``Romy and Michele's
High School Reunion,'' ``Smoke Signals,'' ``The Trigger Effect,''
``Virus,'' ``What's Love Got to Do with It?''
</P>
