<HEADLINE>
POWER FAILURE AFFECTS PAGER SERVICE IN WEST 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ A power failure at a California center
interrupted wireless message service to about 2 million PageNet
customers in the West and Hawaii, the company said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Customers were unable to get messages Monday from 2 to 4 p.m.,
said Scott Baradell, a company spokesman. But usage was likely to
have been light because of the holiday weekend, he said.
</P>
<P>
   People trying to contact PageNet customers by either sending a
voice-mail message or punching in a phone number for a telephone
call back heard a fast busy signal, he said. Service was affected
in Hawaii as well as Alaska, Arizona, California, Colorado, Idaho,
Montana, Nevada, Oregon, Utah, Washington and Wyoming.
</P>
<P>
   Customers with the toll-free 800 or 888 codes were not affected.
The outage occurred at the company's Commerce center in Los Angeles
County.
</P>
<P>
   PageNet is the nation's biggest wireless paging service, with 10
million subscribers worldwide, Baradell said.
</P>
</TEXT>
