<HEADER>
A0583 &Cx1f; taf-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  AM-NYT-BUDGET &LR;      07-06 1035
</HEADER>
<BODY>
 AM-NYT-BUDGET  
(gm) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOR WEDNESDAY AMs &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here are today's top news stories from The New York Times News
Service for AMs of Wednesday, July 7:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; KOSOVO &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-SERBS (Uzice, Yugoslavia) _ Another anti-Milosevic
demonstration is scheduled for today, and momentum seems to be
building after a spontaneous rally Monday night in southern Serbia.
By Blaine Harden.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA (Pristina) _ Russian troops arrive at the airport
here, bringing much-needed supplies to Russian forces. The
commander obliquely acknowledges NATO command. Other developments
in the province's capital. By Carlotta Gall.
</P>
