   EUROPE-TELEVISION (Rome) _ Europe's television industry is in
the grip of an American-style consolidation. Spurred by the the
forces of the global economy and the power of the Internet,
European media companies are forging cross-border links, and
American giants like the Microsoft Corp. are buying into the
action. The resulting corporate alliances are providing a gateway
for advertisers to reach wider mass audiences and an opportunity
for Europe to challenge America's supremacy in television
programming. By John Tagliabue.
