<P>
   CASINOS _ Kentucky, primarly through its incumbent Democratic
governor, is debating whether to bring 15 land-based casinos in to
the state _ pushing the limits of gambling in the very way that the
National Gambling Impact Study Commission recommended against. What
are horse-track-loving Kentuckians saying about this? And what
effect would this have on the gambling in the South, particularly
neighbors Virginia and Tennessee? For one thing, it would be
another squeeze on Tennessee, which allows no gambling. (Manuel,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
