<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Crude oil futures top $20 per barrel for the
first time since November 1997, a signal for energy rigs to get
back to work in Texas and elsewhere. After cutting capital spending
plans from $90 million two years ago to $60 million this year,
Cross Timbers Oil Co. of Fort Worth has decided to boost this
year's spending back up, to as much as $90 million. ``The situation
is looking better for oil and gas prices,'' says Louis Baldwin,
Cross Timbers senior vice president. By DAN PILLER. Story will move
in ``f'' financial category. &QL; 
