   CHAPMAN-TEXAS AT LARGE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GAINESVILLE, Texas _ This Cooke County town of 15,000 has always
been an agricultural center. In the days of the cattle drives, it
was the last stop before Oklahoma Territory; it became a major
supply station for local ranches after the drives dwindled. Cotton
became king; then oil surged from the ground. But baseball was what
got people really excited. When Gainesville prospered, it played
baseball. And it prospered a lot. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved
in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
