   E-TOUR _ ATLANTA _E-Tour, formally Juxtanet, an Atlanta-based
Web firm that allows users who chose the site as their homepage to
see a different site each time they hit the home button. gets $10
million in cash from Jeff Arnold and Bert Ellis, who will also
become board members. We first met juxtanet last year when they
were just a couple of kids in a garage with their friends doing
their PR, now they have a nice pr machine, a new name and some
impressive local backers. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TECH-HEALTHNET _ We went to a number of the healthcare sites on
the Internet, wondering what kind of information would be offered
to an interested, but not expert, consumer. All the sites offer
links to other sources of information. All have lists of suggested
topics and while some had arthritis listed as a subject we could
click on, not all did. To compare, we found their search function,
typed in ''arthritis treatment'' and clicked. Here's some of what
we found. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
