<P>
   BBO-NL-STARS _ National League starters announced, and no Braves
will make it. (Atlanta Jounal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-MARLINS _ ATLANTA _ Braves vs. Florida Marlins game
story. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: First pitch is at 7:40 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-NOTES _ ATLANTA _ Braves notebook. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DOLPHINS-GREEN _ DAVIE, Fla _ Some athletes invest in stocks
and bonds. Willie Green, a 33-year-old receiver who signed with the
Miami Dolphins after being released by Denver in February, chose to
put his money in other commodities. Bermuda grass and sand. About
two years ago, after a couple of attempts to buy existing courses
fell through, Green and nine other investors began building a golf
course on 180 acres in Shelby, N.C., the small town about 35 miles
south of Charlotte that he calls home during the NFL off-season.
(Woods, Palm Beach Post). 20. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FALCONS-CAMP _ Feeling ``Super,'' the Atlanta Falcons gather for
a 3-day mandatory minicamp. (Carvell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   NICKLAUS-HIP _ Jack Nicklaus has withdrawn from this week's U.S.
Senior Open in Des Moines, Iowa, preferring to give his sore left
hip more time to heal. Nicklaus also had to withdraw during the
third round of the Senior Players Championship 10 days ago, marking
just the third time in his 38-year pro career he was unable to
finish a tournament because of injury. Nicklaus, who underwent
hip-replacement surgery Jan. 27, considered playing this week but
decided Monday he's better off taking the conservative route. (Palm
Beach Post). 10.
</P>
