<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Wednesday, July 7 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SMOKE-CRACKDOWN (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles is about to get
serious about the ban on smoking in bars after the ordinance the
City Council passed 18 months ago. Starting this month, the Fire
Department will send inspectors on random sweeps of more than 3,000
bars and restaurants in Los Angeles and investigate complaints to
make sure owners and customers comply with the ban on smoking in
enclosed workplaces. By Deborah Sullivan and Jesse Hiestand. (Will
move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER-FEVER (Los Angeles) _ Soccer fever is here, with the
American women's team in the finals against China and tickets sold
out at the Rose Bowl for what could be record-setting attendance
for any women's sporting event. Scalping _ legal _ aleady is hot
and heavy for the event, which already sold some 85,000 tickets. By
Phillip W. Browne. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news files.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   VALLEY-DREAM (Los Angeles) _ The San Fernando Valley has
developed a case of DreamWorks SKG fever following the studio's
decision to ditch its ill-fated expansion into the marshes north of
Los Angeles International Airport. ``We have started to get a lot
of calls about sites,'' admitted DreamWorks spokesman Andy Spahn on
Tuesday. ``It's hard to say whether they're all serious.'' By Dave
McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
