   SCI-WASHINGTON-DESCENDANTS (Undated) _ Did George Washington
father a son with Venus, a young slave who lived on the estate of
his brother, John Augustine Washington? Three descendants of Venus'
son, who was called West Ford, say that West Ford's father was the
first president of the United States. Historians so far are
skeptical, saying there is no documentary evidence to suggest that
Washington ever met Venus. By Nicholas Wade. (Scheduled to move by
7:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.) 1,800 words.
</P>
