<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HILLARY-CLINTON (Washington) _ Hillary Rodham Clinton takes the
initial step toward running for the Senate, which barely six months
ago considered ousting her husband from office. Her advisers
formally notify the Federal Election Commission that the first lady
has created a committee to fund her exploration of a Senate
campaign from the Empire State. By STEWART M. POWELL. (Already
filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000 (Denver) _ Texas George W. Bush campaigns with
