new president of the teamsters' union, has agreed to hire Stier, a
respected former prosecutor, to set up an in-house anti-corruption
program for the 1.4-million member union. The move is seen as the
first step in an effort to persuade the federal government to end
its decade-long oversight of the teamsters. (Dith Pran/New York
Times Photo)
