has stirred controversy among the immigrant Vietnamese community.
The paintings are, top, ``Young Woman Forging Steel'' by D. Nguyen
and ``Mother's Heart'' by Do Son. Vietnamese immigrants have been
protesting the exhibit of contemporary Vietnamese art since it
opened inside this Spanish-style museum on June 25. (Edward
Carreon/New York Times Photo)
