   Though Bush popularized the phrase, Owens said he has been a
practitioner of compassionate conservatism for years. He cited, for
example, his efforts to reach out to minorities and members of the
Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
   Four members of his cabinet are Democrats, including Larry
Trujillo, director of General Support Services. Trujillo, a former
Democratic state senator, joined other Hispanic Democrats in
announcing their support for Bush.
</P>
<P>
   Owens said reaching across the partisan divide has not been
difficult, since he once worked in Washington for former U.S. Rep.
Jim Wright, a liberal Democrat from Fort Worth who later became
House speaker. The two have been close friends ever since.
(Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
